<TEXT>
<turn speaker="Lyn_Vaughn" spkrtype="female" startTime="1483.443" endTime="1497.586">
 The actors, the set, the special effects, all vital to making movie magic. And u- few films are complete without music. 
<time sec="1491.939"/>
 Laurin Sydney talked with some leading film score composers about the sound of movies.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1501.103" endTime="1511.477">
 To help bring his new underwater thriller Sphere to life, director Barry Levinson tapped composer Elliot Goldenthal to provide his characters with some mood music.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Barry_Levinson" spkrtype="male" startTime="1513.960" endTime="1519.242">
 It's gorgeous, it's beautiful. The underwater world is beautiful. But you also have this sense of foreboding.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Elliot_Goldenthal" spkrtype="male" startTime="1521.284" endTime="1526.452">
 It's one of the best moments, I think, in film making, when you finally can marry the music to the uh picture.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1529.527" endTime="1543.764">
 Elmer Bernstein, a film composer for the past forty years, has scored every genre of film, from the Ten Commandments to the Age of Innocence.
<time sec="1537.582"/>
 [[NS]]
<time sec="1539.674"/>
 Most recently, he collaborated with Francis Ford Coppola on the Rainmaker.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Elmer_Bernstein" spkrtype="male" startTime="1547.073" endTime="1557.014">
 Writing music is something you do in a solitary way. So there comes a time, after all the conversations, where you really go into your studio and you hope uh God is good.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1557.014" endTime="1567.752">
 Composer Michael Kamen, who recently scored the Winter Guest, says he's most merry when working on a romantic score for films like Don Juan DeMarco or Robin Hood.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Michael_Kamen" spkrtype="male" startTime="1570.404" endTime="1577.860">
 The best moments for me are when I get to write the kind of music that I love, which is b- beautiful music, music that makes you feel good.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1579.614" endTime="1589.597">
 Steve Endelman, the composer for such movies as Flirting with Disaster, and the upcoming Shakespeare's Sister, says that each character in a film gets their own musical theme.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Steve_Endelman" spkrtype="male" startTime="1590.829" endTime="1598.724">
 I always think about, okay, how are these themes going to relate as the movie progresses, as characters develop, how will these themes develop.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1598.724" endTime="1606.848">
 As an art form, film scoring is only about seventy-five years old, but there are already some legendary composers and scores.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Barry_Levinson" spkrtype="male" startTime="1608.748" endTime="1619.441">
 When you think about Bernard Herrmann, he started as e- 
<time sec="1611.089"/>
 how, how's a career like this. Your first movie is Citizen Kane, and your last movie is Taxi Driver and in between, all the great Hitchcock films.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Michael_Kamen" spkrtype="male" startTime="1619.441" endTime="1623.764">
 The score for Gone with the Wind, I think, immediately jumps to mind.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Elliot_Goldenthal" spkrtype="male" startTime="1623.764" endTime="1627.878">
 Morricone's Once upon a Time in America is one of the great uh you know, film scores.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Barry_Levinson" spkrtype="male" startTime="1627.878" endTime="1633.643">
 Jerry Goldsmith's score for Papillion, I think is a wonderful, wonderful lyrical score.
</turn>
<turn speaker="Laurin_Sydney" spkrtype="female" startTime="1636.378" endTime="1640.284">
 Laurin Sydney, CNN entertainment news, New York.
</turn>
